if (Keyboard.GetState().IsKeyDown(Keys.Escape)) { this.Exit(); }
in the beginning of update (I believe this is a fair way to do it, isn't it ?) just do:
Platform.Exit(); _suppressDraw = true;
and on windows DX (at least) leads to:
if (_window != null) _window.Dispose(); _window = null; Window = null;
so in the game Update method, if window is used AFTER the call to exit like with something like this:
if (!IsMouseVisible) Mouse.SetPosition(200, 200);
